# NOTE: BB’s “definitely no immaterial realms” is surely incorrect. The abstract aruppa is never, so far as I know, used for the, but is regularly used of the meditation attainments: ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā. Further, sabbaso does not mean “definitely”, rather it is part of the standard formula introducing the formless attainments: sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā
